UN’s Shipping Agency Appoints Sekimizu as Secretary-General

-- B y   A l a r i c   N i g h t i n g a l e
-- 
2011-06-28T12:59:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-28/un-s-shipping-agency-appoints-sekimizu-as-secretary-general.html
The  International Maritime
Organization , the  United Nations ’ shipping agency, named Koji
Sekimizu as its secretary-general.  Sekimizu will take over the role on Jan. 1 for an initial
term of four years, the IMO said in a statement today. He
succeeds Efthimios Mitropoulos, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alaric Nightingale in London at 
 anightingal1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stuart Wallace at 
 swallace6@bloomberg.net  